================================================================================
Third-party dependencies
================================================================================

This software builds on third-party open-source components, each under its own
license (see each crate's own license metadata and the generated SBOM for the
authoritative, version-pinned list). Notable runtime dependencies include:

  - arrow-array, arrow-schema,   (Apache-2.0)     — columnar in-memory data +
    arrow-cast, arrow-csv,                           CSV/JSON/TSV I/O and the
    arrow-json, arrow-ord,                           sort/filter compute kernels
    arrow-select                                     that back the grid
  - parquet                      (Apache-2.0)     — Parquet reader (default local
                                                     engine), ranged + footer stats
  - clap                         (MIT / Apache-2.0)— CLI parsing
  - serde, serde_json            (MIT / Apache-2.0)— serialization
  - thiserror                    (MIT / Apache-2.0)— error handling
  - bytes                        (MIT)            — in-memory Parquet windows
  - unicode-width                (MIT / Apache-2.0)— aligned terminal tables

Optional, feature-gated dependencies (off by default — the lean local reader is
the only default build):

  - datafusion                   (Apache-2.0)     — `sql`: read-only SQL engine
  - apache-avro                  (Apache-2.0)     — `iceberg`: parse Iceberg
                                                     metadata + Avro manifests
  - object_store                 (Apache-2.0 / MIT)— `object-store`: BYO-cred
                                                     s3://, gs://, az:// reads
  - url, futures                 (MIT / Apache-2.0)— `object-store` plumbing
  - axum                         (MIT)            — `serve`: HTTP/JSON API
  - rust-embed                   (MIT)            — `serve`: embed the SPA bundle
  - serde_urlencoded             (MIT / Apache-2.0)— `serve`: grid query params
  - tokio                        (MIT)            — `sql`/`serve`/`object-store`
                                                     async runtime
  - reqwest                      (MIT / Apache-2.0)— `remote`: Lakeleto Cloud seam

A complete, version-pinned dependency manifest with licenses is produced as a
CycloneDX SBOM at release time (see RELEASING.md).
